<?php include "../header/header.php"; ?><html><body><div class="container"><br><h1>Unity Color Class</h1><br><br><b>Unity Color Class:</b><br><br>To change the color of a game object, we can follow one of these procedures:<br><br>	> <code>gameObject.color = Color.blue;</code><br><br>Assign custom color values:<br><br>1. <code>gameObject.color = new Color(1f,0f,0f,.85f);</code><br><br>	>  Here, the Color Constructor takes either 3 or 4 values - RGB and (4th param) Alpha Value for transparency.<br>	>  All the parameters are in float format and only take values from 0.0 to 1.0.<br><br>2. <code>gameObject.color = new Color32(255,0,0,90);</code><br><br>	>  To specifically use 0 to 255 values, use Color32 which takes Byte parameters.<br><br>3. <code>gameObject.color = new Color(255/255,0/255,0/255,90);</code><br><br>	>  Output same as above.</div></body></html><br><br><?php include "../footer/footer.php"; ?>